Those are Known fixes to the CPU problems.




Disable Power Problems and Overclocking with control panel.
Step 1: Press Windows + S, input control panel, and click the search result to open it.
Step 2: Navigate to Hardware and Sound > Power Options and click Change plan settings next to your selected power plan.
Step 3: Click Change advanced power settings to open the Power Options dialog.
Step 4: Expand Processor power management > Maximum processor state and set the values of both On battery and Plugged in as 99% to disable Turbo Boost technology.
